The world lost a legend today. My friend Richard Belzer left us, and leaves a trail of so many good memories and iconic stories. 

I met Richard (and Harlee) years ago through my ex boyfriend, and we all ended up collaborating on several short films, tv pilots, and even on the adventure feature film Santorini Blue. You probably know him best from his long standing role as #DetectiveMunch on all of the NBC series’ Law & Order.

But, more than the projects, he, Harlee, and their daughters were so wonderful to spend time with, supporting each other’s hopes and dreams and enjoying life from California to dreamy Bozouls, France.  There were so many good times and holidays we all shared.

I’ll never forget a small group of us having Christmas dinner together at The Central Park Boathouse, and snow started gently falling. We finished dinner and there was actually a large gondola offering rides across the pond, back to the west side of Manhattan. So, we all got into it and started across the pond. The gondolier started singing and they paid him to stop 😂since they wanted quiet serenity. It was so awesome. We sat in complete silence, just soaking in the night as we glided across the magical pond. Sometimes, your friends are your family when you live far away from where you grew up and can’t make it home. 

I’m so grateful to have so many dear memories with them, and am sending my deepest condolences to Harlee, Jessica and Bree. Thank you for the kindness, generosity and (most often) very irreverent and brilliant humor, Belz.

🎬🎭The New Jersey festival premiere of my new short story film “No Regrets” at Grove Film Festival was pure 🪄. 

Sharing a project that was four years in the making really felt amazing, and was so nervewracking, too! I wasn’t sure how the audience would respond, but the feedback was overwhelmingly kind and blew me away. 

It’s hard to put yourself out there and share original work- as both a filmmaker and as an actress. But, I’m always glad when I do. I always just hope that people have some sort of meaningful take away from watching. 

Thank you to everyone who came to support and enjoy the festival. You were, and always are, soooo appreciated!! I loved watching all of the festival’s Official Selection and meeting so many talented filmmakers, production people and actors. 

It was an incredible night. ✨✨✨✨✨✨

Thank you, Grove Film Festival!
